&lt;p&gt;Consultant Nephrologist - 10PAs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a substantive 10 PA consultant role within South West Thames Renal and Transplantation Unit at Epsom and St Helier University Hospitals NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful appointee will join a team of 22 nephrologists based in a busy regional renal unit at St Helier. The postholder will be responsible for weekly general nephrology clinics at Croydon University Hospital and East Surrey Hospital and for managing a cohort of haemodialysis patients. They will also be involved in managing the adult polycystic kidney disease service and clinics based at St Helier.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All applicants must have full registration with the GMC and be a holder of the Certificate of Completion of Training (CCT) or be within six months of the award of the CCT or equivalent on the date of interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date - 4th December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Fiona HarrisJob titleJoint Clinical DirectorEmail addressfiona.harris1@nhs.netTelephone number02082962384Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates are welcome to visit the department, subject to an appointment being made.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Arrangements for visiting the Trust can be made by contacting the following: Dr Fiona Harris or Dr Ginny Quan, Joint Clinical Directors for Renal Services. Telephone: 0208 296 2384 or email ginny.quan@nhs.net or fiona.harris1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
